     __________________________________________________________________

   Careers with the Natural Resources Conservation Service
   There are several careers available with the Natural Resources
   Conservation Service. They are unique, but have at least one thing in
   common - they require a commitment to protecting the United States'
   soil and water for future generations. Click here for information about
   some of the careers available with the Natural Resources Conservation
   Service.
     __________________________________________________________________

   Applying for Jobs within the Federal Government
     * To learn about jobs within the federal government, visit Federal
       Jobs Central web site.
     * To learn more about work and opportunities within the Natural
       Resources Conservation Service or the US Department of Agriculture,
       visit the national NRCS web site or USDA web site.
     * Click here to visit the U.S. Office of Personnel Management (OPM)
       web page: "Qualification Standards for General Schedule Positions -
       Alphabetical Index by Title."
     * Click here to visit the OPM web page "General Schedule Position
       Classification Standards" Indexed by Series.
     __________________________________________________________________

   Earth Team Logo    Joining the Earth Team, NRCS' Volunteer Program
    The Earth Team is a group of concerned citizens, like you, who are
   interested in learning more about our nation's soil and water resources
   and how to help conserve them. By volunteering for the Earth Team in
   New Jersey, you will work side by side with USDA Natural Resources
   Conservation Service professionals.
